As the "Parliamentary Gazette" was known, on 27 September, the Chairman of the Committee of the Council of the Federation on Economic Policy, Andrei Kutepov, sent a letter to Maxime Oreskin, Minister of Economic Development, and Anton Siluanov, Minister of Finance, inviting him to express his position on the initiatives of Federation entities to improve legislation in support of small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs).
It is time to establish interregional links
The Committee on Economic Policy of the Council of the Federation has compiled information from the regions on their business development and the legalization of self-employed, as well as on the outcome of such programmes.
In their letters, the regions presented the challenges of SME development to the senators and made proposals for improving existing legislation.
"To date, there is insufficient communication between regions, with the result that the business community in all regions of the senators' visit has identified the lack of information on regional programmes for the development of entrepreneurship in the country as a whole," noted Andrei Kutepov.
In an annex to the letter to the Government, he presented a set of positive developments in the regions on the legalization of self-employment and a summary of proposals and issues from the regions (available from the drafting).
In addition to the line ministries, regional summary data are also sent to the heads of regional executive bodies.
The exchange of information on good practices in the regions could give rise to enterprise development as a whole.
The first step towards such an exchange will be to send the information available to the Committee on Economic Policy, the "Parliamentary newspaper" said the Senator.
Useful experience
Today, programmes to support small and medium-sized business actors have been adopted and are being successfully implemented in many regions of the country.
For example, a Centre for the Support of Entrepreneurship is in operation in Wolodvsk region, which, in addition to financial support measures, assists businessmen in the certification of finished products.
In the Ivanov region, a business support system has been developed to implement the principle of one window through multi-function centres.
In Krasnodar province, agricultural consumer cooperatives are provided with grants from the regional budget.
A cluster development centre is in operation in the Orlovsk region.
The Amur region, under the federal project "Achelation of small and medium-sized enterprises," provides for the possibility of subsidizing business incubators established through existing non-State cooperative centres from the federal budget.
A number of other regions have special support measures for youth entrepreneurship.
Self-employed continue to be removed from the shadows
In the view of the regional authorities, a number of legislative changes should be made to support small and medium-sized enterprises more effectively.
For example, the Archangel region proposed replacing the term "self-employment" with "business activities," as this "is most appropriate to the content of the public service to promote self-employment of unemployed citizens."
In the Ivanovskaya region, there is a need for amendments to expand the list of activities provided by self-employed citizens, including activities relating to the separation and repair of housing, long-term construction and physical training.
The Bryan region considers it important to strengthen the control of unscrupulous dairy producers through the Mercury Veterinary System.
And in the Kostrom and Magadan regions, they advocate that the concept of "social entrepreneurship" and the areas of support for social entrepreneurship be incorporated into the legal and regulatory fields.
All proposals from the regions will be taken into account in the preparation of public programmes to support small and medium-sized enterprises, and the most important will be developed in the form of specific legislation.
"All proposals from the regions will be taken into account in the preparation of public programmes to support small and medium-sized enterprises, and the most important will be developed in the form of specific legislation," he assured Andrei Kutepov.
